etween provincial technology policy, school board policy, and school-based practices. The authors consider the ways in which technology policy has become "unplugged" from daily experience, showing that teachers, students, and administrators are part of complex pedagogical and social systems that have been badly served by the enforced and hasty introduction of technology. They also show how small, often unquestioned practices and power relations in schools can create seemingly insurmountable impediments to technological implementation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aEDUCATION / Elementary.2bisacsh1 aJenson, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewis, Brian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLewis, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPenny, Milton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRose, Chloë Brushwood, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRose, Chloë Brushwood, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShapson, Stan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077356042040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773560420423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773560420/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pr